fast.name: 2004 Mazda 6 Sport - Fast & Reliable
fast.description: Unfortunately it is time to pass on my absolutely amazing 2004 Mazda 6 Sport Hatchback! It is in great condition, serviced frequently and well taken care of by our local and trusted mechanic at Advanced Auto in Santa Cruz. Runs perfectly, drove it to Yosemite last week and Anaheim about a month ago with absolutely no problems. Just passed Smog. Great gas mileage and a comfortable ride for road trips. Always received premium gas and oil changes every 3,000 miles.Completely upgraded the sound system with a 12inch kicker subwoofer and new speakers and amp (Sounds Incredible). I also put in a touchscreen Pioneer center display that is bluetooth capable and has a usb hookup for your phone to charge and play music. I also installed a back-up camera! This car has really been well taken care of and I am sad to see it go but I am in need of something a bit bigger. There are some signs of age as you can see in the seats and body and the text in the center screen is starting to fade a bit (See Photos). But these minor cosmetic blemishes are truly only aesthetic and do not take away from how amazing this car drives. There are no mechanical issues at all, sometimes a bit of oil does burn off the engine resulting in a smell but we have confirmed with our mechanic that there is no underlying issue associated with this. It’s fast and reliable and will get you where you need to go in comfort and style.The price is $5250 Obo and please feel free to reach out with ANY questions or to schedule a test drive!

loud.name: 6 string NOT BASS Hofner Ignition Series Violin Electric Guitar
loud.description: Hello,Up for sale is a unique and sought after Hofner Violin six string guitar. I bought it from Guitar Center a number of years ago for a little under 300.00. This instrument sports tea cup knobs which are correct to the antique ones from the past, and look better than the knobs that are normally on these Ignition series guitars, I think. I have not seen the Chinese made Hofner I am selling available, for quite a while.https://www.guitarcenter.com/Hofner/Ignition-Series-Violin-Electric-Guitar.gcFrom Guitar Center's website:The Hofner Ignition Series Violin Electric Guitar is lightweight and easy to love. It features set-neck construction and a full 25.5 scale. The body is made of flamed maple back & sides with a sweet sounding spruce top. Loud enough for acoustic practice, it really shines when plugged in thanks to two mini humbuckers. Hardware includes a floating rosewood bridge with tune-o-matic top for perfect intonation and vintage style tuning machines. Case sold separately.FeaturesUltra-light hollowbody designSet neck constructionSpruce topFlamed-maple back & sidesRosewood fretboard with 22 frets and original Hofner Mother-of-pearl “Stripe” inlaysBound body, fretboard and headstock1-11/16” nut width25.5” scale lengthVintage machine with pearl buttons2 mini humbucking pickupsIndividual pickup volume controlsMaster tone and 3-way toggle selectorRosewood floating bridge with tune-o-matic metal top for sustain, tone and adjustable intonationI can be reached by phone or text.As well as an email.B

famous.name: Famous FS-1 Soprano Ukulele OBO
famous.description: Pretty little soprano, nice build with super-thin mahogany laminate, but with a sound that will rival most sold-wood ukes. Extremely light, with excellent projection and beautiful resonance. The FS-1 is a Japanese build, identical to the Kiwaya KS-1, but sold only to the Japanese market. This older uke has a Rosewood fingerboard, which you won't find in production any longer...the newer ones are walnut.  Nice, low action and great intonation. Friction tuners. Tiny scratch on the headstock, mark on the first fret - see the photos for detail. One-of-a-kind cloth gig bag included. Reasonable offers are welcome.

famous.name: Stella Acoustic guitar 1955 with provenance
famous.description: 1955-ish Stella, Letter of Authenticity from his heirs, owned by Terry Teene who was the opening act for Buddy Holly and was there that famous night “the music died” in Iowa. Includes his one hit 45 record Curse of the Hearse and Pussy Galore. Other songs include: Happiness is Coming, (which he recorded under the name of Blaine Bel Aire), and We're Going to put Iowa on the Map. Terry's personal favorites are Fun To Be With and Perfect 36.He also opened for Kenny Rogers, Loretta Lynn, Larry Gatlin, Rick Dees, The Solid Gold Dancers and Dolly Parton were all the featured performers.He performed with Alice Cooper, Nazerath, Flo and Kinks, S H A N A N A, Knack, Cheap Trick, Bobby Vee and many, many more.He is in the Rockabilly Hall of Fame.  Was the 1st Ronald MacDonald. Good to fair condition, no case.He also appeared on dozens of TV shows.

famous.name: Fender '64 Vibroverb Custom 40-Watt 1x15" Guitar Combo 2003 - 2008
famous.description: Fender Vibroverb Custom Shop 64 Cesar Diaz Mod Srv 1964 signature model JBL D130 New old stock speaker upgrade.  FENDER '64 REISSUE VIBROVERB CUSTOM SHOP CESAR DIAZ SRV MODS We just got in this amazing Fender '64 Vibroverb Custom Shop Amplifier with the Stevie Ray Vaughan Mod designed by Cesar Diaz. This amplifier was hand build in the Corona California Custom Shop. It looks and sounds amazing! It is in great shape. It looks as good as any new amplifier we get in stock from Fender!! It has been very well taken care of and has been played very little. All original paper work and hang tags are included. Also included is the original Fender Amplifier Cover. More specs from Fender below. If you have any questions please feel free to let us know!The ‘64 Vibroverb Custom amplifier is a modern interpretation of a Fender legend. With this amp, guitarists can enjoy the original Blackface Fender tones heard on countless Country, Jazz and Rock recordings. Then, with the flip of a couple of switches, “modify” the amp to create cranked-up tones bristling with sustain and harmonics. These Vibroverb modifications were perfected by César Diaz, world famous “Amp Doctor,” who worked closely with Fender during the inception of this new model. Original 1964 Vibroverbs are hard–to–find collectables, and are particularly prized by players who enjoy the “Texas Blues” style. Your brand new Vibroverb will allow you to put a fresh spin on a classic theme.Two fully independent channels, each with input jacks for normal- and high-gain instruments40 watts output power into 8Ω or 4ΩSelectable TUBE or solid-state DIODE rectifierSelectable STOCK or MODIFIED amp configurationAll–tube circuitry (STOCK amp configuration selected)6L6 GE (Power amp) tubes, 12AX7A (Preamp, Vibrato) tubes, 12AT7 (Reverb, Phase–splitter) tubes , 5AR4 (Rectifier) tubeTwo-button Footswitch (included) for remote on/off control of Reverb and VibratoHand-wired “Eyelet Board” circuitFinger–jointed pine cabinetTilt-back cabinet legs for easy monitoring
